## 12) SCENE WRITING FORMAT

Use this exact format for each storyboard scene after the hook:

#### **SCENE [#] — [approx. time range]**
[3–5 sentences of highly visual, cinematic description that can be directly converted into an image-generation prompt.]

Each scene must clearly describe:
- environment / setting
- main subject
- exact action
- props / objects
- emotional tone
- lighting / atmosphere
- composition / framing
- story function in that moment
- what new pressure, failure, consequence, reaction, realization, or correction is being revealed

Avoid vague phrasing like:
- “he struggles”
- “things go wrong”
- “it’s hard”

Also avoid scenes that only show movement between places unless that movement itself adds story pressure or consequence.

Show exactly what is happening visually.

